authorizations_search.Name: authorizations_search
authorizations_search.Description: This table contains information about all the transactions in sales and their details like status, date, network, payment methods etc. keywords Auth, Sale, Flow, Transaction

a_approvalCode.Name: a_approvalCode
a_approvalCode.Description: Identifies if the authorization was approved or declined.

a_type.Name: a_type
a_type.Description: Transaction type code e.g., sale, refund etc.

a_transactionDateTime.Name: a_transactionDateTime
a_transactionDateTime.Description: Date & time of the authorization transaction.

a_accountNumber.Name: a_accountNumber
a_accountNumber.Description: Card number used for authorization transaction.

a_amount.Name: a_amount
a_amount.Description: Amount requested for the authorization transaction.

a_currency.Name: a_currency
a_currency.Description: Currency code used for the transaction.

a_network.Name: a_network
a_network.Description: Name of the authorizing network associated with the transaction.

a_paymentMethod.Name: a_paymentMethod
a_paymentMethod.Description: Identifies the method of payment used on the transaction.
a_paymentMethod.Examples: It contains values : "Manual", "Mobile & ECommerce", "Credential on File".

a_declineReason.Name: a_declineReason
a_declineReason.Description: Identifies the decline reason for the transaction.

a_authCode.Name: a_authCode
a_authCode.Description: Authorization code from association(s). Generally, 6/7 alphanumeric code that gets printed on the receipt.

a_siteID.Name: a_siteID
a_siteID.Description: An unique identifier assigned to the merchant. Also known as a MID.

a_merchantCategory.Name: a_merchantCategory
a_merchantCategory.Description: Identifies the standard merchant category code assigned to the transaction.

a_giftCardNumber.Name: a_giftCardNumber
a_giftCardNumber.Description: Gift card number used for authorization transaction.

a_sendMode.Name: a_sendMode
a_sendMode.Description: Indicates store and forward mode of the transaction.

a_mobileWallet.Name: a_mobileWallet
a_mobileWallet.Description: Identifies wallet type indicator (e.g., Apple Pay, Samsung Pay, Google Pay, etc.).

a_ECIIndicator.Name: a_ECIIndicator
a_ECIIndicator.Description: Indicates the electronic commerce indicator used for the transaction.
a_ECIIndicator.Examples: It contains values : "Channel Encrypted E-Comm", "Recurring Transaction", "No ECI Provided", "Secure E-Comm", "Non-Secure E-Comm".

a_terminalID.Name: a_terminalID
a_terminalID.Description: Identifies terminal identifier for the transaction.

a_CAVVResponse.Name: a_CAVVResponse
a_CAVVResponse.Description: Identifies name verification result response from the authorizer.
a_CAVVResponse.Examples: It contains values : "Not Validated", "Not Validated - Erroneous Data", "Passed Validation", "Issuer Does Not Participate", "Failed Validation - Attempt".

a_AVSResponse.Name: a_AVSResponse
a_AVSResponse.Description: Identifies the result, obtained from the cardholder's name, during address verification.
a_AVSResponse.Examples: It contains values : "Not Provided", "Address & Zip Match", "Address & Zip Does Not Match", "Card Type Not Supported", "Information/System Not Available", "Retry", "Addr Only (Discover: Addr & Zip) Match", "Zip Matches, Address Does Not", "9 Digit Zip Matches, Address Does Not".

a_CVVResult.Name: a_CVVResult
a_CVVResult.Description: Identifies the card verification value (CVV2) response from the authorizer.
a_CVVResult.Examples: It contains values : "Not Provided", "Match/Passed Validation", "No Match/Failed Validation", "Issuer Attempted/Not Complete".

a_banknetRef.Name: a_banknetRef
a_banknetRef.Description: Indicates Mastercard assigned Banknet reference number.

a_subType.Name: a_subType
a_subType.Description: Transaction sub type codes e.g., Pin, Signature, etc.

a_cardGroup.Name: a_cardGroup
a_cardGroup.Description: The group of the card that is used in the transaction.

a_nativeRejectCode.Name: a_nativeRejectCode
a_nativeRejectCode.Description: The reject code as received from the front-end switches.

a_linkResponseCode.Name: a_linkResponseCode
a_linkResponseCode.Description: Identifies the Card N/w (i.e., VISA, Mastercard, Discover, AMEX) link response.

a_DCCIND.Name: a_DCCIND
a_DCCIND.Description: Identifies the acceptance of dynamic currency code transaction processing.

a_DCCCurrency.Name: a_DCCCurrency
a_DCCCurrency.Description: Identifies non-local merchant enabled dynamic currency code.

a_DCCAmount.Name: a_DCCAmount
a_DCCAmount.Description: Identifies the total transaction amount in the currency of the card rather than in the currency of the place of purchase.

a_assocRespCode.Name: a_assocRespCode
a_assocRespCode.Description: Identifies the initial association response code for the transaction.

a_merchandiseCode.Name: a_merchandiseCode
a_merchandiseCode.Description: Describes the type of fuel purchased.

a_fuelPurchaseLocation.Name: a_fuelPurchaseLocation
a_fuelPurchaseLocation.Description: Identifies whether the fuel was purchased at the pump or In-Store

a_quantity.Name: a_quantity
a_quantity.Description: Indicates the quantity of gas in gallons purchased.

a_lcldt.Name: a_lcldt
a_lcldt.Description: Local date time of the transaction.

a_cshbAmount.Name: a_cshbAmount
a_cshbAmount.Description: Cash back amount provided for the transaction.

a_first6.Name: a_first6
a_first6.Description: First six digits of card number.

a_last4.Name: a_last4
a_last4.Description: Last four digits of card number.

a_paypalAccountNumber.Name: a_paypalAccountNumber
a_paypalAccountNumber.Description: PayPal account number used for authorization transaction.

a_referenceNumber.Name: a_referenceNumber
a_referenceNumber.Description: Authorizer retrieval reference number, a unique RRN issued by the authorizer for each transaction.

a_seqno.Name: a_seqno
a_seqno.Description: A unique reference number assigned to a transaction by the merchant, and will be returned as is in the response message if exist.

a_fraudScore.Name: a_fraudScore
a_fraudScore.Description: Indicates the fraud score on the transaction.

a_timeTaken.Name: a_timeTaken
a_timeTaken.Description: Indicates time taken to send a transaction to issuer.

a_settleCutOffTime.Name: a_settleCutOffTime
a_settleCutOffTime.Description: Cutoff time setup for settlement of transaction(s) for a Merchant.

a_recurring.Name: a_recurring
a_recurring.Description: Describes the recurrence type for the transaction.

a_networkInputIndicator.Name: a_networkInputIndicator
a_networkInputIndicator.Description: Identifies the value that merchant sent in the cardholder ID field as PAN or NT.

a_networkAuthIndicator.Name: a_networkAuthIndicator
a_networkAuthIndicator.Description: Identifies if auth was performed with PAN or NT - 1st Try.
a_networkAuthIndicator.Examples: It contains values : "Primary Account Number", "Network Token".

a_networkAuthIndicator2.Name: a_networkAuthIndicator2
a_networkAuthIndicator2.Description: Identifies if auth was performed with PAN or NT - 2nd Try.

a_networkAuthIndicator3.Name: a_networkAuthIndicator3
a_networkAuthIndicator3.Description: Identifies if auth was performed with PAN or NT - 3rd

a_bankFiid.Name: a_bankFiid
a_bankFiid.Description: Identifies the bank FIID for a financial institution or customer.

a_termCapCode.Name: a_termCapCode
a_termCapCode.Description: Identifies the transaction capabilities of the terminal associated with the transaction.

a_mktSpecificDataInd.Name: a_mktSpecificDataInd
a_mktSpecificDataInd.Examples: It contains values : "Unknown / Not Provided", "Bill payment".

a_cardLevelResult.Name: a_cardLevelResult
a_cardLevelResult.Description: Result obtained from the account type & track data type information supplied by the issuer.

a_cavvDowngradeReason.Name: a_cavvDowngradeReason
a_cavvDowngradeReason.Description: Identifies the Mastercard CAVV downgrade reason.

a_posTermCap.Name: a_posTermCap
a_posTermCap.Description: Identifies the term-cap sent in the initial or original authorization request.

a_productAmount.Name: a_productAmount
a_productAmount.Description: Identifies the amount of the item described in this record.

a_productQuantity.Name: a_productQuantity
a_productQuantity.Description: Identifies the number of units in the transaction.

a_productUnitPrice.Name: a_productUnitPrice
a_productUnitPrice.Description: Identifies the unit price of the product described in this record.

a_dccCountryCode.Name: a_dccCountryCode
a_dccCountryCode.Description: Identifies the country in which the acquiring institution resides.

a_dccRate.Name: a_dccRate
a_dccRate.Description: Identifies the non-US currency conversion rate used to convert the value of total transaction amount to the value of DCC amount.

a_voucherNumber.Name: a_voucherNumber
a_voucherNumber.Description: Identifies the voucher number in the transaction.

a_lodgingArrivalDate.Name: a_lodgingArrivalDate
a_lodgingArrivalDate.Description: Identifies the check-in date in the transaction.

a_lodgingDuration.Name: a_lodgingDuration
a_lodgingDuration.Description: Identifies the number of days of lodging in the transaction.

a_lodgingAmount.Name: a_lodgingAmount
a_lodgingAmount.Description: Identifies the room rate for Amex or the total authorized amount for Visa.

a_lodgingChargeType.Name: a_lodgingChargeType
a_lodgingChargeType.Description: Identifies the charge type or preferred customer indicator/no show indicator.

a_folioNumber.Name: a_folioNumber
a_folioNumber.Description: Identifies the portfolio number associated with the transaction.

a_unpredictableNumber.Name: a_unpredictableNumber
a_unpredictableNumber.Description: Identifies a random number generated by the device to add additional variability to the cryptogram.

a_terminalSerialNumber.Name: a_terminalSerialNumber
a_terminalSerialNumber.Description: Identifies the Interface Device (IFD) serial number.

a_issuerScriptResults.Name: a_issuerScriptResults
a_issuerScriptResults.Description: Identifies the results of script processing.

a_issuerScript1.Name: a_issuerScript1
a_issuerScript1.Description: Identifies the issuer script commands the issuer sends to the card in the response.

a_tppVarID.Name: a_tppVarID
a_tppVarID.Description: Identifies the third-party processor or value added reseller involved in the transaction.

a_partialApprovalFlag.Name: a_partialApprovalFlag
a_partialApprovalFlag.Description: Indicates whether partial approval processing is supported.

a_crossBorderIndicator.Name: a_crossBorderIndicator
a_crossBorderIndicator.Description: Indicates whether the transaction qualifies as a fee program transaction.

a_recordNumber.Name: a_recordNumber
a_recordNumber.Description: This internal number is the unique identifier on the OmniPay platform for the authorizations.

a_posConditionCode.Name: a_posConditionCode
a_posConditionCode.Examples: It contains values : "Unknown", "Card Verification Required", "Mail/Phone/Recurring Order", "ECI-Open Network Transaction", "Internet Only Recurring (PINless)".

a_messageTypeIdentifier.Name: a_messageTypeIdentifier
a_messageTypeIdentifier.Description: Message type identifier (MTID) of the response message.

a_masterCardBanknetDt.Name: a_masterCardBanknetDt
a_masterCardBanknetDt.Description: Identifies the date of the authorization response received from MasterCard.

a_addendumNumber.Name: a_addendumNumber
a_addendumNumber.Description: Used in conjunction to the item no to uniquely identify a record.

a_vatReferenceNumber.Name: a_vatReferenceNumber
a_vatReferenceNumber.Description: Identification number assigned by the taxing authorities to the purchasing company.

a_rentalAgreementNumber.Name: a_rentalAgreementNumber
a_rentalAgreementNumber.Description: Invoice number of original rental agreement.

a_rentalState.Name: a_rentalState
a_rentalState.Description: The state, county or province where the rented car was picked up.

a_rentalReturnLocationID.Name: a_rentalReturnLocationID
a_rentalReturnLocationID.Description: Address, phone number, etc. Identifying rental return location

a_rentalReturnState.Name: a_rentalReturnState
a_rentalReturnState.Description: State where the car was returned to the rental agency.

a_rentalReturnCountry.Name: a_rentalReturnCountry
a_rentalReturnCountry.Description: Country where the car was returned to the rental agency.

a_extraChargeAmount.Name: a_extraChargeAmount
a_extraChargeAmount.Description: Additional charges added to customer bill after check-out.

a_velocityIndicator.Name: a_velocityIndicator
a_velocityIndicator.Description: Indicating whether this record is under Velocity controls.

a_serverId.Name: a_serverId
a_serverId.Description: Indicates server Id for certain types of transactions like eating joints.

a_posData.Name: a_posData
a_posData.Description: Identifies Card N/w (i.e., VISA, Mastercard, Discover, AMEX) POS data.

a_cardNetworkDataError.Name: a_cardNetworkDataError
a_cardNetworkDataError.Description: Identifies a MasterCard Banknet® data error (track, POS, or MasterCard transaction category code error) for the transaction.

a_cardNetworkCVCError.Name: a_cardNetworkCVCError
a_cardNetworkCVCError.Description: Identifies Banknet® interchange data returned by MasterCard, indicating an invalid card validation code.

a_salesTaxAmount.Name: a_salesTaxAmount
a_salesTaxAmount.Description: Identifies the amount of sales tax in the transaction.

a_freightAmount.Name: a_freightAmount
a_freightAmount.Description: Identifies the amount of freight charges in the transaction.

a_dutyAmount.Name: a_dutyAmount
a_dutyAmount.Description: Identifies the amount of duty charges in the transaction.

a_emvAppCryptogram.Name: a_emvAppCryptogram
a_emvAppCryptogram.Description: Identifies the online card authentication cryptogram generated by the card during the transaction.

a_emvAppInterchangeProfile.Name: a_emvAppInterchangeProfile
a_emvAppInterchangeProfile.Description: Identifies a series of indicators reflecting the specific functions supported by the chip card application.

a_emvAppTxnCounter.Name: a_emvAppTxnCounter
a_emvAppTxnCounter.Description: Identifies the counter from the card. Used to identify possible fraud.

a_emvChipAuthResult.Name: a_emvChipAuthResult
a_emvChipAuthResult.Description: Identifies the card authentication results for a chip card.

a_emvChipTxnInd.Name: a_emvChipTxnInd
a_emvChipTxnInd.Description: Identifies if it is a chip transaction.

a_emvExpDate.Name: a_emvExpDate
a_emvExpDate.Description: Identifies the expiration date of the application.

a_emvIssuerAppData.Name: a_emvIssuerAppData
a_emvIssuerAppData.Description: Identifies the various card-related data which is transmitted from the issuer.

a_emvTermCountryCode.Name: a_emvTermCountryCode
a_emvTermCountryCode.Description: Identifies the country where the merchant device is located.

a_emvTermVerificationResult.Name: a_emvTermVerificationResult
a_emvTermVerificationResult.Description: Identifies the results of risk management performed by the device.

a_emvCVMResult.Name: a_emvCVMResult
a_emvCVMResult.Description: Identifies the Cardholder Verification Method (CVM) used for the transaction.

a_emvCryptoInfoData.Name: a_emvCryptoInfoData
a_emvCryptoInfoData.Description: Identifies the type of Application Cryptogram (AC) carried in the transaction.

a_emvTxnType.Name: a_emvTxnType
a_emvTxnType.Description: Identifies the type of EMV financial transaction as represented by the first two digits of the processing code.

a_emvTermCapProfile.Name: a_emvTermCapProfile
a_emvTermCapProfile.Description: Identifies the card data input, Cardholder Verification Method (CVM) & the security capabilities supported by the chip terminal.

a_emvDedicatedFileName.Name: a_emvDedicatedFileName
a_emvDedicatedFileName.Description: Identifies the Application Identifier (AID) of the chip application.

a_emvIssuerAuthData.Name: a_emvIssuerAuthData
a_emvIssuerAuthData.Description: Identifies the issuer authentication data sent by the issuer to the card in the authorization response.

a_txnCatCode.Name: a_txnCatCode
a_txnCatCode.Description: Identifies the category code of the transaction.

a_shipmentToZip.Name: a_shipmentToZip
a_shipmentToZip.Description: Identifies the ZIP + 4 post office code in the shipping destination address.

a_shipmentFromZip.Name: a_shipmentFromZip
a_shipmentFromZip.Description: Identifies the ZIP + 4 post office code in the shipping source address.

a_shipmentToCountryCode.Name: a_shipmentToCountryCode
a_shipmentToCountryCode.Description: Identifies the post office country code in the shipping destination address.

a_purchaseCode.Name: a_purchaseCode
a_purchaseCode.Description: Identifies the merchant’s purchase order number.

a_serviceCode.Name: a_serviceCode
a_serviceCode.Description: Value determines if card is chip capable.

a_taxRate.Name: a_taxRate
a_taxRate.Description: Rate used to generate VAT/tax amount on freight/shipping.

a_lineItemTotal.Name: a_lineItemTotal
a_lineItemTotal.Description: Line item total. May be zero for zero cost items.

a_authResponseCode.Name: a_authResponseCode
a_authResponseCode.Description: Identifies the response code from the authorizer.

a_formFactor.Name: a_formFactor
a_formFactor.Description: Identifies the form factor in the chip.

a_entryModeIndicator.Name: a_entryModeIndicator
a_entryModeIndicator.Description: Identifies the account number method of data entry, the PIN pad capabilities.

a_debitFeeAmount.Name: a_debitFeeAmount
a_debitFeeAmount.Description: Identifies amount of the debit fees.

a_reversed.Name: a_reversed
a_reversed.Description: Contains the character Y if the authorization has been reversed else N.

a_tipAmount.Name: a_tipAmount
a_tipAmount.Description: Applicable for certain types of transactions, like eating joints.

a_merchantAdviceCode.Name: a_merchantAdviceCode
a_merchantAdviceCode.Examples: It contains values : "Unknown", "Will never approve", "Cannot approve currently", "Additional data available", "Revocation of Authorization Order".

a_nativeExprProvider.Name: a_nativeExprProvider
a_nativeExprProvider.Description: Native value for host-based discount value based on the relationship.

a_exprProvider.Name: a_exprProvider
a_exprProvider.Description: Host based discount value based on the relationship.

a_onlineTxnInd.Name: a_onlineTxnInd
a_onlineTxnInd.Description: Indicating whether this transaction came via online or batch server (compass)

a_networkTokenOfferingType.Name: a_networkTokenOfferingType
a_networkTokenOfferingType.Description: Network Token Program Participation - Offering Type

a_drdRegulatorIndicator.Name: a_drdRegulatorIndicator
a_drdRegulatorIndicator.Description: Signifies if the BIN if is regulated or unregulated

a_drdNetwork.Name: a_drdNetwork
a_drdNetwork.Description: The two digit network ID that was routed to for Authorization

cb_siteID.Name: cb_siteID
cb_siteID.Description: Site ID (BE) - merchant number associated with each the business location.

cb_authNetwork.Name: cb_authNetwork
cb_authNetwork.Description: Authorization network of the credit card utilized for the transaction.

cb_receivedDate.Name: cb_receivedDate
cb_receivedDate.Description: Date when the chargeback was initiated.

cb_statusDate.Name: cb_statusDate
cb_statusDate.Description: Date for an expected response to the client.

cb_transactionDate.Name: cb_transactionDate
cb_transactionDate.Description: Original date on a transaction that is being disputed and associated with a specific chargeback.

cb_workType.Name: cb_workType
cb_workType.Examples: It contains values : "Outgoing Pre-Arbitration", "First Chargeback", "Incoming Pre-Arbitration", "First Chargeback Reversal".

cb_winLoss.Name: cb_winLoss
cb_winLoss.Description: Status of dispute, describing if it has been won, loss or pending.

cb_Reason.Name: cb_Reason
cb_Reason.Description: Descriptive reason associated with a specific chargeback.

cb_ReasonKey.Name: cb_ReasonKey
cb_ReasonKey.Description: Descriptive reason associated with a specific chargeback. (Code)

cb_adjustmentAmountSign.Name: cb_adjustmentAmountSign
cb_adjustmentAmountSign.Description: Sign for adjustment amount that is being disputed.

cb_currency.Name: cb_currency
cb_currency.Description: Currency code used for the transaction.

cb_chargebackAmount.Name: cb_chargebackAmount
cb_chargebackAmount.Description: Chargeback amount that is disputed by cardholder.

cb_dueDate.Name: cb_dueDate
cb_dueDate.Description: A Chargeback due date is the deadline that you must respond by, in order to dispute a chargeback.

cb_transactionType.Name: cb_transactionType
cb_transactionType.Description: Transaction type that identifies the transactions as a sale/refund etc.

cb_Disposition.Name: cb_Disposition
cb_Disposition.Description: Describing final settlement of a chargeback.
cb_Disposition.Examples: It contains values : "Case has been reversed", "Status Update to Closed", "Your case response has been rejected", "Adjustment to Merchant", "Close Case", "Merchant Accepted Case".

cb_ECIndicator.Name: cb_ECIndicator
cb_ECIndicator.Description: Electronic Commerce Indicator (ECI) is a value returned by Visa, MasterCard, JCB, and American Express etc. indicating the outcome of authentication attempted on transactions.
cb_ECIndicator.Examples: It contains values : "Recurring Transaction", "No ECI Provided", "Channel Encrypted E-Comm", "Secure E-Comm", "Single Payment Transaction (MOTO)".

cb_transactionAmount.Name: cb_transactionAmount
cb_transactionAmount.Description: Transaction amount that is being disputed.

cb_adjustmentAmount.Name: cb_adjustmentAmount
cb_adjustmentAmount.Description: Adjustment amount that is being disputed.

cb_accountNumber.Name: cb_accountNumber
cb_accountNumber.Description: Card number used for the transaction.

cb_first6.Name: cb_first6
cb_first6.Description: First six digits of card number.

cb_last4.Name: cb_last4
cb_last4.Description: Last four digits of card number.

cb_invoiceNumber.Name: cb_invoiceNumber
cb_invoiceNumber.Description: Invoice number associated with the inquiry.

cb_disputeID.Name: cb_disputeID
cb_disputeID.Description: Case number associated with a specific chargeback.

cb_referenceNumber.Name: cb_referenceNumber
cb_referenceNumber.Description: Reference number associated with the inquiry.

cb_authCode.Name: cb_authCode
cb_authCode.Description: Authorization code from association(s). Generally, 6/7 alphanumeric code that gets printed on the receipt.

cb_trackingNumber.Name: cb_trackingNumber
cb_trackingNumber.Description: The tracking number of the disputed transaction.

cb_merchantCategory.Name: cb_merchantCategory
cb_merchantCategory.Description: Identifies the standard merchant category code assigned to the transaction.
cb_merchantCategory.Examples: It contains values : "Large Merchant Digital Goods (5818)", "Fast Food Restaurants (5814)".

cb_paymentMethod.Name: cb_paymentMethod
cb_paymentMethod.Description: Identifies the method of payment used on the transaction.

cb_sendMode.Name: cb_sendMode
cb_sendMode.Description: Indicates store and forward mode of the transaction.

cb_recurring.Name: cb_recurring
cb_recurring.Description: Describes the recurrence type for the transaction.

cb_mobileWallet.Name: cb_mobileWallet
cb_mobileWallet.Description: Identifies wallet type indicator (e.g., Apple Pay, Samsung Pay, Google Pay etc.).

cb_userData.Name: cb_userData
cb_userData.Description: Discretionary data sent on transaction by the merchant.

cb_batchDate.Name: cb_batchDate
cb_batchDate.Description: Date group of transactions was settled.

cb_batchNumber.Name: cb_batchNumber
cb_batchNumber.Description: Number assigned to each group of settled transactions.

cb_softDescriptor.Name: cb_softDescriptor
cb_softDescriptor.Description: Available for PFAC (Payment Facilitator Aggregator) only. Name of the Sub Merchant.

cb_submittedTxnCurrencyCode.Name: cb_submittedTxnCurrencyCode
cb_submittedTxnCurrencyCode.Description: ISO 4217 3 digit code representing the currency the transaction was processed in at the POS.

cb_origTranCurrency.Name: cb_origTranCurrency
cb_origTranCurrency.Description: Transaction amount of the original presentment in transaction currency.

cb_merchantSettleAmount.Name: cb_merchantSettleAmount
cb_merchantSettleAmount.Description: The amount settled with the merchant for the original presentment (that is, the amount posted to the merchant account), before the deduction of any charges.

cb_networkSettleCurrency.Name: cb_networkSettleCurrency
cb_networkSettleCurrency.Description: Currency settled with the payment network for the presentment before the deduction of any charges.

cb_networkSettleAmount.Name: cb_networkSettleAmount
cb_networkSettleAmount.Description: Amount settled with the payment network for the presentment (that is, the interchange settlement amount), before the deduction of any charges.

cb_origSlipNumber.Name: cb_origSlipNumber
cb_origSlipNumber.Description: The OmniPay internal slip number of the original presentment.

cb_itemSlipNumber.Name: cb_itemSlipNumber
cb_itemSlipNumber.Description: The OmniPay internal slip number of the transaction (that is, of the 1st chargeback, representment, and so on).

cb_memberMessageText.Name: cb_memberMessageText
cb_memberMessageText.Description: Text supplied by the issuer with the incoming first or second chargeback, it can also be the text send with the REP. This is empty for items related to transfers.

cb_documentIndicator.Name: cb_documentIndicator
cb_documentIndicator.Description: Indicates if a document was provided for the item type. This data is extracted from the original base II or IPM file and only populated for chargebacks items (1st and 2nd).

cb_retrievalRequestId.Name: cb_retrievalRequestId
cb_retrievalRequestId.Description: Since this feed do not include RRQ this field is always empty.

cb_chargebackReferenceId.Name: cb_chargebackReferenceId
cb_chargebackReferenceId.Description: The issuer reference number (Chargeback Control Number/CCN) for the transaction.

cb_centralProcessingDate.Name: cb_centralProcessingDate
cb_centralProcessingDate.Description: Central processing date of the latest incoming transaction for the chargeback case.

cb_partialAmountFlag.Name: cb_partialAmountFlag
cb_partialAmountFlag.Description: Flag to indicate if the issuer has identified this chargeback as a partial chargeback.

cb_vmeAdditionalAuthMethod.Name: cb_vmeAdditionalAuthMethod
cb_vmeAdditionalAuthMethod.Description: V.me additional auth method from the original presentment.

cb_vmeAdditionalAuthReasonCode.Name: cb_vmeAdditionalAuthReasonCode
cb_vmeAdditionalAuthReasonCode.Description: V.me additional auth reason code from the original presentment.

cb_ppolProgramData.Name: cb_ppolProgramData
cb_ppolProgramData.Description: PPOL program data from the original presentment.

cb_originalChargebackSlipNumber.Name: cb_originalChargebackSlipNumber
cb_originalChargebackSlipNumber.Description: If the item type is a 1st or 2nd chargeback this field is equal to the field item_slip, but for presentment and transfer this field will indicate which is the related chargeback.

cb_omnipayClienNumber.Name: cb_omnipayClienNumber
cb_omnipayClienNumber.Description: This is the OmniPay client number and is the link to the MP feed.

cb_merchantFundingCurrency.Name: cb_merchantFundingCurrency
cb_merchantFundingCurrency.Description: Currency in which the original presentment was funded to the merchant.

cb_merchantFUndingAmount.Name: cb_merchantFUndingAmount
cb_merchantFUndingAmount.Description: Only populated for some item type with the content of the field dependent on the item type.

cb_authRecordSequence.Name: cb_authRecordSequence
cb_authRecordSequence.Description: This is a link to the AU.REC_ID and may be empty. If filled it is the suggested matching authorization details that matches the original presentment.

cb_previousTransferToMerchant.Name: cb_previousTransferToMerchant
cb_previousTransferToMerchant.Description: Y (True) if there was a previous transfer to a merchant account when the item type is REP, TWA, TWS. For other item types it will always be N (false).

cb_uniqueTransactionId.Name: cb_uniqueTransactionId
cb_uniqueTransactionId.Description: Unique transaction identifier will be generated at point of sale before the transaction is sent for authorization or offline approval.

cb_chargebackCycle.Name: cb_chargebackCycle
cb_chargebackCycle.Description: Specific processing cycle of a presentment or a chargeback.

cb_CAVVResponseCode.Name: cb_CAVVResponseCode
cb_CAVVResponseCode.Description: Identifies name verification result response from the authorizer.
cb_CAVVResponseCode.Examples: It contains values : "Not Validated", "Not Validated - Erroneous Data", "Issuer Does Not Participate", "Failed Validation - Attempt".

fd_siteID.Name: fd_siteID
fd_siteID.Description: An unique identifier assigned to the merchant. Also known as a MID.

fd_fundedDate.Name: fd_fundedDate
fd_fundedDate.Description: Date when the funding to/from the merchant associated with this transaction.

fd_batchNo.Name: fd_batchNo
fd_batchNo.Description: Batch number (batch that pulled this settlement transaction to initiate thee funding) for the transaction.

fd_majorCategory.Name: fd_majorCategory
fd_majorCategory.Description: Identifies the major category for the merchant.
fd_majorCategory.Examples: It contains values : "Chargebacks", "Chargeback Reversals", "Deposits", "Financial Adjustments", "Interchange Charges", "Service Charges", "Fee".

fd_minorCategory.Name: fd_minorCategory
fd_minorCategory.Description: Identifies the minor category for the merchant.

fd_productCode.Name: fd_productCode
fd_productCode.Description: Name of the authorizing network associated with the transaction.
fd_productCode.Examples: It contains values : "MASTERCARD", "VISA", "DEBIT CARD", "MISCELLANEOUS", "AMEX", "DISCOVER", "ELECTRONIC BENEFITS TRANSFER".

fd_creditAmount.Name: fd_creditAmount
fd_creditAmount.Description: Indicates the credit amount on the transaction.

fd_debitAmount.Name: fd_debitAmount
fd_debitAmount.Description: Indicates the debit amount on the transaction.

fd_currency.Name: fd_currency
fd_currency.Description: Currency code used for the transaction.

fd_referenceNumber.Name: fd_referenceNumber
fd_referenceNumber.Description: Acquirer reference number. This is only available for the transaction Type: chargeback.

fd_ddaLast4.Name: fd_ddaLast4
fd_ddaLast4.Description: Last four digits of DDA number.

fd_recordDate.Name: fd_recordDate
fd_recordDate.Description: This is pipeline date when the data was loaded.

fd_tranAmount.Name: fd_tranAmount
fd_tranAmount.Description: Amount requested for the authorization transaction.

fd_itemCount.Name: fd_itemCount
fd_itemCount.Description: Indicates the item count on the transaction.

fd_depositTypeCd.Name: fd_depositTypeCd
fd_depositTypeCd.Examples: It contains values : "Chargebacks Reversals", "Net Sales", "Adjustments", "I/C Charges", "Paid by Others", "Service Charges", "Fees".

fd_bankReferenceNo.Name: fd_bankReferenceNo
fd_bankReferenceNo.Description: Unique number in merchant's bank deposit for funding.

fd_tranTypeCode.Name: fd_tranTypeCode
fd_tranTypeCode.Description: This is the transaction type code associated to the acquirer commission charge.

fd_addendumARN.Name: fd_addendumARN
fd_addendumARN.Description: ARN created by transferring a transaction or by Misc. batch input.

fd_feeSeqCode.Name: fd_feeSeqCode
fd_feeSeqCode.Description: Fee sequence code for a transaction.

fd_feeSeqDesc.Name: fd_feeSeqDesc
fd_feeSeqDesc.Description: Fee sequence description per fee sequence code.

fd_tranCategoryDesc.Name: fd_tranCategoryDesc
fd_tranCategoryDesc.Description: Description for the transaction category code.

fd_relatedSourceTran.Name: fd_relatedSourceTran
fd_relatedSourceTran.Description: Details of related transactions within the FA feed.

fd_localAmount.Name: fd_localAmount
fd_localAmount.Description: The gross amount posted to the account, in the local currency.

fd_accountCurrentNet.Name: fd_accountCurrentNet
fd_accountCurrentNet.Description: The net amount in the account currency.

fd_accountID.Name: fd_accountID
fd_accountID.Description: Unique identifier for the merchant account.

fd_accountType.Name: fd_accountType
fd_accountType.Description: The type of the account i.e., Payment Account Retail (PAR).

fd_paymentStatus.Name: fd_paymentStatus
fd_paymentStatus.Description: Payment status using funding warehouse functionality.

fd_accountCurrencyGross.Name: fd_accountCurrencyGross
fd_accountCurrencyGross.Description: Gross amount posted to the account.

fd_intraAccountRefNo.Name: fd_intraAccountRefNo
fd_intraAccountRefNo.Description: Reference number that indicate what transaction are related to intra account settlement.

fd_countLimit.Name: fd_countLimit
fd_countLimit.Description: Indicates the number of times the payment instructions should be executed, zero means indefinite.

fd_amountLimit.Name: fd_amountLimit
fd_amountLimit.Description: Indicates a limit amount to be collected, for example for factoring payment instruction, zero means unlimited.

fd_startDate.Name: fd_startDate
fd_startDate.Description: Indicates when the payment instruction will stop being executed.

fd_endDt.Name: fd_endDt
fd_endDt.Description: Indicates when the payment instruction will start to be executed.

fd_executionCount.Name: fd_executionCount
fd_executionCount.Description: Indicates the number of times the payment instruction was executed.

fd_factorAgent.Name: fd_factorAgent
fd_factorAgent.Description: Free text, can be used to enter the name of the person that authorized the instruction.

fd_lastExecutionDate.Name: fd_lastExecutionDate
fd_lastExecutionDate.Description: Indicates the last time the payment instruction was evaluated.

fd_merchantIdShort.Name: fd_merchantIdShort
fd_merchantIdShort.Description: This column contains the internal OmniPay unique client number. This is the unique identifier on this feed.

fd_note.Name: fd_note
fd_note.Description: Free text entered by the user when setting up the payment instruction

fd_paymentBaseAmt.Name: fd_paymentBaseAmt
fd_paymentBaseAmt.Description: Indicate a fixed based amount to be deducted from the account

fd_paymentMaximumAmt.Name: fd_paymentMaximumAmt
fd_paymentMaximumAmt.Description: Indicates a maximum amount to be collected, if the percentage of the balance is greater than this amount. The amount is expressed in the account currency

fd_paymentMinimumAmt.Name: fd_paymentMinimumAmt
fd_paymentMinimumAmt.Description: Indicates a minimum amount to be collected, if the percentage of the balance is less than this amount. The amount is expressed in the account currency

fd_paymentPercent.Name: fd_paymentPercent
fd_paymentPercent.Description: Indicates the percentage that will be taken from the balance of the account

fd_period.Name: fd_period
fd_period.Description: Indicates how often the payment instruction is executed.

st_first6.Name: st_first6

st_last4.Description: Last four digits of card number.

st_currency.Description: Processing currency code used for the transaction.

st_authCurrency.Description: Currency code used for the transaction.

st_transactionStatus.Description: Transaction processing status associated with the settle transaction.

st_paymentMethod.Description: Identifies the method of payment used on the transaction.

st_entryModeSource.Description: The last byte from POS_ENTRY_MODE which tells us the PIN capability.

st_acquirerRefNo.Description: Acquirer reference #: An ARN in credit card transactions is the Acquirer reference number, a unique no that tags a credit card txn when it goes from the merchant's bank (acquiring bank) through the card network to the cardholders bank (the issuer).

st_visaPrdtId.Name: st_visaPrdtId
st_visaPrdtId.Description: A value returned by Visa, to designate the type of card product used to process the transaction.

st_mcPrdtId.Name: st_mcPrdtId
st_mcPrdtId.Description: A value returned by MasterCard, to designate the type of card product used to process the transaction.

st_merchantCategory.Name: st_merchantCategory
st_merchantCategory.Description: Identifies the standard merchant category code assigned to the transaction.

st_ECIIndicator.Name: st_ECIIndicator

st_transactionSource.Description: How the transaction was sent to us for processing.

st_iCFeePerTranRate.Name: st_iCFeePerTranRate

st_networkSecurityFeePerTranAmount.Name: st_networkSecurityFeePerTranAmount

st_authorizationType.Examples: It contains values : "EBT Food Stamp Ð Purchase", "EBT Food Stamp Ð Merchandise Refund", "Pre-paid Approval", "Retail Purchase", "Debit Refund", "Business Debit".

st_reclassCd.Name: st_reclassCd

st_bankReferenceNumber.Name: st_bankReferenceNumber
st_bankReferenceNumber.Description: Unique number in merchant's bank deposit for funding.
